events.description: The Senate of Rome says that Caesar will be declared a public enemy unless he disbands his army, prompting the tribunes who support him to flee to where Caesar is waiting in Ravenna.
events.html: • 49 BC – The Senate of Rome says that Caesar will be declared a public enemy unless he disbands his army, prompting the tribunes who support him to flee to where Caesar is waiting in Ravenna.[1]

events.description: Afonso IV becomes King of Portugal.
events.html: • 1325 – Afonso IV becomes King of Portugal.[2]

events.description: French troops, led by Francis, Duke of Guise, take Calais, the last continental possession of England.
events.html: • 1558 – French troops, led by Francis, Duke of Guise, take Calais, the last continental possession of England.[3]

events.description: Fire destroys Jamestown, Virginia.
events.html: • 1608 – Fire destroys Jamestown, Virginia.[4]

events.description: Galileo Galilei makes his first observation of the four Galilean moons: Ganymede, Callisto, Io and Europa, although he is not able to distinguish the last two until the following night.
events.html: • 1610 – Galileo Galilei makes his first observation of the four Galilean moons: Ganymede, Callisto, Io and Europa, although he is not able to distinguish the last two until the following night.[5]

events.description: Battle of Zlatoust: Battle between Bashkir and Tatar rebels and the government troops of the Tsardom of Russia. It is one of the events of the Bashkir rebellion of 1704–1711.
events.html: • 1708 – Battle of Zlatoust: Battle between Bashkir and Tatar rebels and the government troops of the Tsardom of Russia. It is one of the events of the Bashkir rebellion of 1704–1711.[6]

events.description: Bashkir rebels besiege Yelabuga.
events.html: • 1708 – Bashkir rebels besiege Yelabuga.[7]

events.description: A peace treaty is signed between Peshwa Bajirao and Jai Singh II following Maratha victory in the Battle of Bhopal.
events.html: • 1738 – A peace treaty is signed between Peshwa Bajirao and Jai Singh II following Maratha victory in the Battle of Bhopal.[8]

events.description: The first American commercial bank, the Bank of North America, opens.
events.html: • 1782 – The first American commercial bank, the Bank of North America, opens.[9]

events.description: Frenchman Jean-Pierre Blanchard and American John Jeffries travel from Dover, England, to Calais, France, in a gas balloon.
events.html: • 1785 – Frenchman Jean-Pierre Blanchard and American John Jeffries travel from Dover, England, to Calais, France, in a gas balloon.[10]

events.description: HMS Beagle, with Charles Darwin on board, drops anchor off the Chonos Archipelago.
events.html: • 1835 – HMS Beagle, with Charles Darwin on board, drops anchor off the Chonos Archipelago.[11]

events.description: The Kingstree jail fire kills 22 freedmen in Reconstruction-era South Carolina.
events.html: • 1867 – The Kingstree jail fire kills 22 freedmen in Reconstruction-era South Carolina.[12]

events.description: Thomas Edison makes a kinetoscopic film of someone sneezing. On the same day, his employee, William Kennedy Dickson, receives a patent for motion picture film.
events.html: • 1894 – Thomas Edison makes a kinetoscopic film of someone sneezing.[13] On the same day, his employee, William Kennedy Dickson, receives a patent for motion picture film.[14]

events.description: The distress signal "CQD" is established only to be replaced two years later by "SOS".
events.html: • 1904 – The distress signal "CQD" is established only to be replaced two years later by "SOS".[15]

events.description: A workers riot in Rio Blanco, Veracruz leaves many people dead and injured while demanding better working conditions.
events.html: • 1907 – A workers riot in Rio Blanco, Veracruz leaves many people dead and injured while demanding better working conditions.[16]

events.description: Montenegrin guerrilla fighters rebel against the planned annexation of Montenegro by Serbia, but fail.
events.html: • 1919 – Montenegrin guerrilla fighters rebel against the planned annexation of Montenegro by Serbia, but fail.[17]

events.description: The New York State Assembly refuses to seat five duly elected Socialist assemblymen.
events.html: • 1920 – The New York State Assembly refuses to seat five duly elected Socialist assemblymen.[18]

events.description: Dáil Éireann ratifies the Anglo-Irish Treaty by a 64–57 vote.[citation needed]
events.html: • 1922 – Dáil Éireann ratifies the Anglo-Irish Treaty by a 64–57 vote.[citation needed]

events.description: The first transatlantic commercial telephone service is established from New York City to London.
events.html: • 1927 – The first transatlantic commercial telephone service is established from New York City to London.[19]

events.description: A disastrous flood of the River Thames kills 14 people and causes extensive damage to much of riverside London.
events.html: • 1928 – A disastrous flood of the River Thames kills 14 people and causes extensive damage to much of riverside London.[20]

events.description: Guy Menzies flies the first solo non-stop trans-Tasman flight (from Australia to New Zealand) in 11 hours and 45 minutes, crash-landing on New Zealand's west coast.
events.html: • 1931 – Guy Menzies flies the first solo non-stop trans-Tasman flight (from Australia to New Zealand) in 11 hours and 45 minutes, crash-landing on New Zealand's west coast.[21]

events.description: Benito Mussolini and French Foreign minister Pierre Laval sign the Franco-Italian Agreement.
events.html: • 1935 – Benito Mussolini and French Foreign minister Pierre Laval sign the Franco-Italian Agreement.[22]

events.description: Winter War: Battle of Raate Road: The Finnish 9th Division finally defeat the numerically superior Soviet forces on the Raate-Suomussalmi road.
events.html: • 1940 – Winter War: Battle of Raate Road: The Finnish 9th Division finally defeat the numerically superior Soviet forces on the Raate-Suomussalmi road.[23]

events.description: Kentucky Air National Guard pilot Thomas Mantell crashes while in pursuit of a supposed UFO.
events.html: • 1948 – Kentucky Air National Guard pilot Thomas Mantell crashes while in pursuit of a supposed UFO.[24]

events.description: In the Sverdlovsk air disaster, all 19 of those on board are killed, including almost the entire national ice hockey team (VVS Moscow) of the Soviet Air Force
events.html: • 1950 – In the Sverdlovsk air disaster, all 19 of those on board are killed, including almost the entire national ice hockey team (VVS Moscow) of the Soviet Air Force – 11 players, as well as a team doctor and a masseur.[25]

events.description: Georgetown–IBM experiment: The first public demonstration of a machine translation system is held in New York at the head office of IBM.
events.html: • 1954 – Georgetown–IBM experiment: The first public demonstration of a machine translation system is held in New York at the head office of IBM.[26]

events.description: Contralto Marian Anderson becomes the first person of color to perform at the Metropolitan Opera in Giuseppe Verdi's Un ballo in maschera.
events.html: • 1955 – Contralto Marian Anderson becomes the first person of color to perform at the Metropolitan Opera in Giuseppe Verdi's Un ballo in maschera.[27]

events.description: The United States recognizes the new Cuban government of Fidel Castro.
events.html: • 1959 – The United States recognizes the new Cuban government of Fidel Castro.[28]

events.description: Surveyor program: Surveyor 7, the last spacecraft in the Surveyor series, lifts off from Cape Canaveral Launch Complex 36A.
events.html: • 1968 – Surveyor program: Surveyor 7, the last spacecraft in the Surveyor series, lifts off from Cape Canaveral Launch Complex 36A.[29]

events.description: Iberia Flight 602 crashes near Ibiza Airport, killing all 104 people on board.
events.html: • 1972 – Iberia Flight 602 crashes near Ibiza Airport, killing all 104 people on board.[30]

events.description: In his second shooting spree of the week, Mark Essex fatally shoots seven people and wounds five others at Howard Johnson's Hotel in New Orleans, before being shot to death by police officers.
events.html: • 1973 – In his second shooting spree of the week, Mark Essex fatally shoots seven people and wounds five others at Howard Johnson's Hotel in New Orleans, before being shot to death by police officers.[31]

events.description: Third Indochina War: Cambodian–Vietnamese War: Phnom Penh falls to the advancing Vietnamese troops, driving out Pol Pot and the Khmer Rouge.
events.html: • 1979 – Third Indochina War: Cambodian–Vietnamese War: Phnom Penh falls to the advancing Vietnamese troops, driving out Pol Pot and the Khmer Rouge.[32]

events.description: U.S. President Jimmy Carter authorizes legislation giving $1.5 billion in loans to bail out the Chrysler Corporation.
events.html: • 1980 – U.S. President Jimmy Carter authorizes legislation giving $1.5 billion in loans to bail out the Chrysler Corporation.[33]

events.description: Brunei becomes the sixth member of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
events.html: • 1984 – Brunei becomes the sixth member of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).[34]

events.description: Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency launches Sakigake, Japan's first interplanetary spacecraft and the first deep space probe to be launched by any country other than the United States or the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1985 – Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency launches Sakigake, Japan's first interplanetary spacecraft and the first deep space probe to be launched by any country other than the United States or the Soviet Union.[35]

events.description: Sutton United, a team in the fifth tier of English league football, defeated top-tier Coventry City in one of the biggest upsets in FA Cup history.
events.html: • 1989 – Sutton United, a team in the fifth tier of English league football, defeated top-tier Coventry City in one of the biggest upsets in FA Cup history.[36]

events.description: Roger Lafontant, former leader of the Tonton Macoute in Haiti under François Duvalier, attempts a coup d'état, which ends in his arrest.
events.html: • 1991 – Roger Lafontant, former leader of the Tonton Macoute in Haiti under François Duvalier, attempts a coup d'état, which ends in his arrest.[37]

events.description: The Fourth Republic of Ghana is inaugurated with Jerry Rawlings as president.
events.html: • 1993 – The Fourth Republic of Ghana is inaugurated with Jerry Rawlings as president.[38]

events.description: Bosnian War: The Bosnian Army executes a surprise attack at the village of Kravica in Srebrenica.
events.html: • 1993 – Bosnian War: The Bosnian Army executes a surprise attack at the village of Kravica in Srebrenica.[39]

entities.name: Armed Forces of Bosnia and Herzegovina

events.description: A British Aerospace Jetstream 41 operating as United Express Flight 6291 crashes in Gahanna, Ohio, killing five of the eight people on board.
events.html: • 1994 – A British Aerospace Jetstream 41 operating as United Express Flight 6291 crashes in Gahanna, Ohio, killing five of the eight people on board.[40]

events.description: The Senate trial in the impeachment of U.S. President Bill Clinton begins.
events.html: • 1999 – The Senate trial in the impeachment of U.S. President Bill Clinton begins.[41]

events.description: A hot air balloon crashes near Carterton, New Zealand, killing all 11 people on board.
events.html: • 2012 – A hot air balloon crashes near Carterton, New Zealand, killing all 11 people on board.[42]

events.description: Two gunmen commit mass murder at the offices of Charlie Hebdo in Paris, shooting twelve people execution style, and wounding eleven others.
events.html: • 2015 – Two gunmen commit mass murder at the offices of Charlie Hebdo in Paris, shooting twelve people execution style, and wounding eleven others.[43]

events.description: A car bomb explodes outside a police college in the Yemeni capital Sana'a with at least 38 people reported dead and more than 63 injured.
events.html: • 2015 – A car bomb explodes outside a police college in the Yemeni capital Sana'a with at least 38 people reported dead and more than 63 injured.[44]

events.description: The 6.4Mw  2019–20 Puerto Rico earthquakes kill four and injure nine in southern Puerto Rico.
events.html: • 2020 – The 6.4Mw  2019–20 Puerto Rico earthquakes kill four and injure nine in southern Puerto Rico.[45]

events.description: The United States Congress certifies the results of 2020 United States presidential election, confirming the election of Joe Biden, on the morning of the 7th after the Capitol was attacked the day before during earlier attempts to certify the election by supporters of the incumbent president Donald Trump, who lost re-election to Biden and attempted to overturn the results of the election.
events.html: • 2021 – The United States Congress certifies the results of 2020 United States presidential election, confirming the election of Joe Biden, on the morning of the 7th after the Capitol was attacked the day before during earlier attempts to certify the election by supporters of the incumbent president Donald Trump, who lost re-election to Biden and attempted to overturn the results of the election.[46]

entities.name: Attempts to overturn the 2020 United States presidential election

events.description: The longest U.S. House of Representatives speaker election since the December 1859
events.html: • 2023 – The longest U.S. House of Representatives speaker election since the December 1859 – February 1860 U.S. speaker election concludes and Kevin McCarthy is elected 55th Speaker of the United States House of Representatives.[47][48]
